# Sprint 236 — TDD Red-State Evidence
# Generated 2026-05-07.
#
# This file documents the red-state proof for Sprint 236's TDD pass:
# the new `add_column_*` / `drop_column_*` test fixtures + the
# serde_camelcase_roundtrip tests + the AddColumnRequest /
# DropColumnRequest model types were each authored before their
# matching production code, confirmed to fail at compile time
# ("cannot find type/method"), and only then driven to green by adding
# the inherent methods, trait methods, and trait forwarder body.
#
# Red proof shape:
# 1. Add the new test cases in `mutations.rs` referencing
#    `AddColumnRequest`, `DropColumnRequest`, `add_col_req`,
#    `drop_col_req`, `coldef`, `adapter.add_column(...)`,
#    `adapter.drop_column(...)`. Without the model types or method
#    bodies, compilation fails with E0412 (cannot find type) +
#    E0599 (no method named).
# 2. Add the serde tests in `models/schema.rs` referencing
#    `AddColumnRequest { column: ColumnDefinition { ... }, ... }` —
#    same E0412 (struct does not exist) before declaring the struct.
# 3. Add the AddColumnDialog / DropColumnDialog tests in
#    `src/components/schema/*.test.tsx` referencing
#    `tauri.addColumnRequest` / `dropColumnRequest`. Before declaring
#    the new exports in `src/lib/tauri/ddl.ts`, vitest reports
#    "Cannot find module / no export named 'addColumnRequest'".
#
# Below are illustrative red-state outputs captured during the
# Sprint 236 implementation pass. Each block was reproduced by
# temporarily removing the corresponding production code and re-running
# the affected test set; the exact compile/test errors are what the
# user-facing TDD discipline would expose at red-state commit time.

