## Backend red — byte-string mismatch on full-combo case

Once the inherent method exists but emission order is wrong (e.g.
`DEFAULT` before `NOT NULL`), the byte-string fixture fails:

```
$ cargo test --lib add_column_preview_full_combo_byte_equivalent
running 1 test
test add_column_preview_full_combo_byte_equivalent ... FAILED

failures:

---- add_column_preview_full_combo_byte_equivalent stdout ----
thread 'add_column_preview_full_combo_byte_equivalent' panicked at
'assertion `left == right` failed
  left: "ALTER TABLE \"public\".\"users\" ADD COLUMN \"age\" int DEFAULT 0 NOT NULL CHECK (age >= 0)"
 right: "ALTER TABLE \"public\".\"users\" ADD COLUMN \"age\" int NOT NULL DEFAULT 0 CHECK (age >= 0)"',
src/db/postgres/mutations.rs:??:??
```

The locked emission order `<name> <type> [NOT NULL] [DEFAULT <expr>]
[CHECK (<expr>)]` is enforced by this test — drift trips it.

## Frontend red — `addColumnRequest is not a function`

```
$ pnpm vitest run src/components/schema/AddColumnDialog.test.tsx

FAIL  src/components/schema/AddColumnDialog.test.tsx
  ✕ AddColumnDialog (Sprint 236) > [AC-236-04] opens with empty name + empty type

  TypeError: tauri.addColumnRequest is not a function
   ❯ src/components/schema/AddColumnDialog.tsx:???:??
```

Resolved by adding `addColumnRequest` / `dropColumnRequest` to
`src/lib/tauri/ddl.ts` and re-exporting via `src/lib/tauri/index.ts`.

